# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: ArrivingInAlGahaem
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah looked out over the edge of the cart, spying through the metal bars that kept her trapped inside."
    new "Sarah looked out over the edge of the cart, spying through the metal bars that kept her trapped inside."

    old "She had known for a while that they had been drawing closer to Al'Gahaem, the sounds of the city had been carried on the wind, meeting them as they neared the city."
    new "She had known for a while that they had been drawing closer to Al'Gahaem, the sounds of the city had been carried on the wind, meeting them as they neared the city."

    old "Before, all she could see was the same, from day to day. Desert, stretching out as far as the horizon."
    new "Before, all she could see was the same, from day to day. Desert, stretching out as far as the horizon."

    old "She was recently sure they had been on the road for a little over two weeks, but one day bled into the next, and with little distraction, she dared not even be certain of that."
    new "She was recently sure they had been on the road for a little over two weeks, but one day bled into the next, and with little distraction, she dared not even be certain of that."

    old "But now distraction was all she could see."
    new "But now distraction was all she could see."

    old "Al'Gahaem was truly a city, and yet, so very different from the capital in Rosanna."
    new "Al'Gahaem was truly a city, and yet, so very different from the capital in Rosanna."

    old "The cart rode across a broad stone brick road which was so full it had to stop on more than on occasion."
    new "The cart rode across a broad stone brick road which was so full it had to stop on more than on occasion."

    old "On each end of the large road, tents, hovels and the rare sandstone house, all weaved together."
    new "On each end of the large road, tents, hovels and the rare sandstone house, all weaved together."

    old "As if the city was some chaotic thing, alive in the way that a beehive could be called alive. All across it, the people swarmed and moved, seemingly random, and yet, each with purpose."
    new "As if the city was some chaotic thing, alive in the way that a beehive could be called alive. All across it, the people swarmed and moved, seemingly random, and yet, each with purpose."

    old "Sarah quickly concluded that Al'Gahaem was a city which existed by success."
    new "Sarah quickly concluded that Al'Gahaem was a city which existed by success."

    old "Unlike the capital in Rosanna, which stood for centuries, seeing good times and bad times but always persisting, Al'Gahaem spawned out of the succes of Hassar's conquests."
    new "Unlike the capital in Rosanna, which stood for centuries, seeing good times and bad times but always persisting, Al'Gahaem spawned out of the succes of Hassar's conquests."

    old "And just as easily, she figured, it would likely fade back into the desert should the good times end."
    new "And just as easily, she figured, it would likely fade back into the desert should the good times end."

    old "This was a city that existed because it willed to exist and needed to exist."
    new "This was a city that existed because it willed to exist and needed to exist."

    old "And so roads were construced, tents build, hovels quickly put up, all growing organically to the surging demand."
    new "And so roads were construced, tents build, hovels quickly put up, all growing organically to the surging demand."

    old "Passing by a building on the side of the road, Sarah saw a crowd of people, waving up their hands, shouting out bids."
    new "Passing by a building on the side of the road, Sarah saw a crowd of people, waving up their hands, shouting out bids."

    old "On the stage, she saw five people, each close to her age, chained to the wooden floor, naked save for the shackles that kept them their."
    new "On the stage, she saw five people, each close to her age, chained to the wooden floor, naked save for the shackles that kept them their."

    old "Each seemed to have the same defeated look on their face, mostly staring down or out into the vague distance."
    new "Each seemed to have the same defeated look on their face, mostly staring down or out into the vague distance."

    old "Even naked, it was obvious to Sarah. These were her countrymen, being sold as slaves."
    new "Even naked, it was obvious to Sarah. These were her countrymen, being sold as slaves."

    old "Al'Gahaem was as city that grew no crops, mined no ores, and had no industry to speak of. They existed off their plunder, which meant above all other things, slaves."
    new "Al'Gahaem was as city that grew no crops, mined no ores, and had no industry to speak of. They existed off their plunder, which meant above all other things, slaves."

    old "Sarah felt a sting of pain in her heart."
    new "Sarah felt a sting of pain in her heart."

    old "To bear the fate that had fallen on her was one thing, but to know that so many in her nation now suffered like she did, it was enough to tear her apart."
    new "To bear the fate that had fallen on her was one thing, but to know that so many in her nation now suffered like she did, it was enough to tear her apart."

    old "She sat back down, having seen enough of this horrid city for now. She tried to find comfort in feeling of the cart weaving from side to side."
    new "She sat back down, having seen enough of this horrid city for now. She tried to find comfort in feeling of the cart weaving from side to side."

    old "Some time later, they came to a halt."
    new "Some time later, they came to a halt."

    old "The sounds of the city had grown louder and louder. Sarah suspected they were drawing close to somewhere."
    new "The sounds of the city had grown louder and louder. Sarah suspected they were drawing close to somewhere."

    old "The door to the wagon opened."
    new "The door to the wagon opened."

    old "The officer stood in the opening, he had a distracted look on his face."
    new "The officer stood in the opening, he had a distracted look on his face."

    old "Off to the side, he was shouting commands at some men. He snapped his finger at Sarah, urging her to come to him. She dutifully did."
    new "Off to the side, he was shouting commands at some men. He snapped his finger at Sarah, urging her to come to him. She dutifully did."

    old "Jaeid stood in the opening, a stern look on his face."
    new "Jaeid stood in the opening, a stern look on his face."

    old "Sarah, we've arrived."
    new "Sarah, we've arrived."

    old "Arrived where?"
    new "Arrived where?"

    old "The house of the Khan, Hassar's palace."
    new "The house of the Khan, Hassar's palace."

    old "What do you want me to do?"
    new "What do you want me to do?"

    old "Sarah begged him with her eyes for any help he could offer her."
    new "Sarah begged him with her eyes for any help he could offer her."

    old "Trust in me, in what I've told you, and you will be fine."
    new "Trust in me, in what I've told you, and you will be fine."

    old "She knew she had no other options."
    new "She knew she had no other options."

    old "She pushed herself off the wooden floor of the cart and walked towards Jaeid."
    new "She pushed herself off the wooden floor of the cart and walked towards Jaeid."

    old "I know, appearances."
    new "I know, appearances."

    old "She said it and turned around, letting him seize her by the arm. She could feel he tried to be gentle with her."
    new "She said it and turned around, letting him seize her by the arm. She could feel he tried to be gentle with her."

    old "Under the watchful eye of her chaperone, she stepped out of the cart."
    new "Under the watchful eye of her chaperone, she stepped out of the cart."

    old "All around her, people were rushing off in different directions. Busy. Everything was so busy here."
    new "All around her, people were rushing off in different directions. Busy. Everything was so busy here."

    old "What most surprised her was how little she seemed to matter to any of them."
    new "What most surprised her was how little she seemed to matter to any of them."

    old "A naked woman in Rosanna would bring the street to a stop, but here, she barely seemed to solicit more than a quick appreciative glance."
    new "A naked woman in Rosanna would bring the street to a stop, but here, she barely seemed to solicit more than a quick appreciative glance."

    old "The hand around her arm pulled on her, reminding her to keep walking."
    new "The hand around her arm pulled on her, reminding her to keep walking."

    old "Out in front of her was the great palace."
    new "Out in front of her was the great palace."

    old "It lived up to its name."
    new "It lived up to its name."

    old "The palace was oddly flat, with the exclusion of several spires off the corners of the construction, reaching up to the heavens."
    new "The palace was oddly flat, with the exclusion of several spires off the corners of the construction, reaching up to the heavens."

    old "But for the lack of its height, it made up by stretching far beyond even Sarah could see."
    new "But for the lack of its height, it made up by stretching far beyond even Sarah could see."

    old "Build entirely out of sandstone, the great palace seemed almost as if it had been carved out of the earth itself. Sarah wondered, if that might not just have been the case."
    new "Build entirely out of sandstone, the great palace seemed almost as if it had been carved out of the earth itself. Sarah wondered, if that might not just have been the case."

    old "As she was dragged up the stairs, Sarah tried her best to keep up with the march, keeping her balance with every step."
    new "As she was dragged up the stairs, Sarah tried her best to keep up with the march, keeping her balance with every step."

    old "The people leaving and entering the great palace were like a surge in both directions. One misstep and Sarah figured they would carry her off like the current in the sea."
    new "The people leaving and entering the great palace were like a surge in both directions. One misstep and Sarah figured they would carry her off like the current in the sea."

    old "Stepping into the castle, a cooling shade descended on her skin."
    new "Stepping into the castle, a cooling shade descended on her skin."

    old "There were few windows, leaving the great palace feeling oddly muted in its colours, but also keeping the punishing desert heat out."
    new "There were few windows, leaving the great palace feeling oddly muted in its colours, but also keeping the punishing desert heat out."

    old "Sarah was grateful for this fact, because she doubted she could survive even a single day of full exposure to this sun."
    new "Sarah was grateful for this fact, because she doubted she could survive even a single day of full exposure to this sun."

    old "As they continued further into the castle, Sarah began to notice just how many different peoples were here."
    new "As they continued further into the castle, Sarah began to notice just how many different peoples were here."

    old "In Rosanna, most everyone was from Rosanna, but here, all the people's from all the corners of the world seemed to mingle in one large hive."
    new "In Rosanna, most everyone was from Rosanna, but here, all the people's from all the corners of the world seemed to mingle in one large hive."

    old "All so very busy."
    new "All so very busy."

    old "When Sarah was finally dragged into the last room, she didn't need to be told to realize that this was the throne room."
    new "When Sarah was finally dragged into the last room, she didn't need to be told to realize that this was the throne room."

    old "The room stretched so far in each direction, that it almost seemed hard to see the other side."
    new "The room stretched so far in each direction, that it almost seemed hard to see the other side."

    old "The floor was filled with people sitting in circles, discussing, bartering, debating."
    new "The floor was filled with people sitting in circles, discussing, bartering, debating."

    old "In this room, her nakedness was more novel and more observed, and Sarah felt herself grow more conscious of it."
    new "In this room, her nakedness was more novel and more observed, and Sarah felt herself grow more conscious of it."

    old "Near the end of the hall, following a long line, did one arive at the great hall, and sitting there, atop his throne, was a man."
    new "Near the end of the hall, following a long line, did one arive at the great hall, and sitting there, atop his throne, was a man."

    old "A man whose name she had heard many times by now, and whose appearance lived up to his reputation. Hassar."
    new "A man whose name she had heard many times by now, and whose appearance lived up to his reputation. Hassar."

    old "He possesed a body unlike any she had ever seen."
    new "He possesed a body unlike any she had ever seen."

    old "He stood so tall that he matched all other men in size by at least a head."
    new "He stood so tall that he matched all other men in size by at least a head."

    old "His size was only further complimented by the broad shoulders. He stood over most other men as most other men stood over women."
    new "His size was only further complimented by the broad shoulders. He stood over most other men as most other men stood over women."

    old "The colour of his skin was a deep brown, etched by both genes and sun, is seemed to Sarah like clay baked over."
    new "The colour of his skin was a deep brown, etched by both genes and sun, is seemed to Sarah like clay baked over."

    old "His black hair was slicked back and his face filled in by a beard in that same ink black."
    new "His black hair was slicked back and his face filled in by a beard in that same ink black."

    old "His colossal arms only confirmed to Sarah what every other part of him suggested. This man could break Sarah in half and not even break a sweat."
    new "His colossal arms only confirmed to Sarah what every other part of him suggested. This man could break Sarah in half and not even break a sweat."

    old "He sat atop the throne with an ease, leaning back and occasionally speaking to advisors on his side as he waved forward and waved away, one petitioner after the other."
    new "He sat atop the throne with an ease, leaning back and occasionally speaking to advisors on his side as he waved forward and waved away, one petitioner after the other."

    old "Instantly, Sarah could see that Hassar was a man who took to command, and wielded power with a natural ease that had always escaped the men in her life."
    new "Instantly, Sarah could see that Hassar was a man who took to command, and wielded power with a natural ease that had always escaped the men in her life."

    old "Sarah noticed a ring on Hassar's finger, glowing with a bright crimson glow."
    new "Sarah noticed a ring on Hassar's finger, glowing with a bright crimson glow."

    old "It was oddly like that colour, and yet, it also struck Sarah as somehow uniquely distinct, as if she had never seen anything like it before."
    new "It was oddly like that colour, and yet, it also struck Sarah as somehow uniquely distinct, as if she had never seen anything like it before."

    old "She turned to Jaeid in whisper."
    new "She turned to Jaeid in whisper."

    old "What's what?"
    new "What's what?"

    old "The ring on his finger...I've never seen a gemstone with a colour like that."
    new "The ring on his finger...I've never seen a gemstone with a colour like that."

    old "Suddenly, Jaeid's grip tightened around her arm, his fingers digging deep into her skin, hurting her."
    new "Suddenly, Jaeid's grip tightened around her arm, his fingers digging deep into her skin, hurting her."

    old "She turned to Jaeid with a shocked expression, but too afraid to say anything."
    new "She turned to Jaeid with a shocked expression, but too afraid to say anything."

    old "Sarah, promise me that you will not speak of that to him."
    new "Sarah, promise me that you will not speak of that to him."

    old "I'll tell you later, but if he asks, promise me that you will tell him that the stone on his ring is black, as black as obsidian."
    new "I'll tell you later, but if he asks, promise me that you will tell him that the stone on his ring is black, as black as obsidian."

    old "For the first time, she seemed to detect genuine fear in this man who always seemed so in control of his emotions."
    new "For the first time, she seemed to detect genuine fear in this man who always seemed so in control of his emotions."

    old "Promise me, Sarah, please."
    new "Promise me, Sarah, please."

    old "He kept his voice down for fear of being overheard."
    new "He kept his voice down for fear of being overheard."

    old "I promise..."
    new "I promise..."

    old "This vow seemed to calm Jaeid down."
    new "This vow seemed to calm Jaeid down."

    old "Good, good."
    new "Good, good."

    old "Oh, and Sarah, I'm sorry, but I'll push you in just a moment."
    new "Oh, and Sarah, I'm sorry, but I'll push you in just a moment."

    old "Hassar wants those he conquers to fall down at his throne, I'll try not to hurt you too much."
    new "Hassar wants those he conquers to fall down at his throne, I'll try not to hurt you too much."

    old "This man, she thought, seemed to live at the tyrant's every whim. Could he be a good man, even if he worked for the man that enslaved her people?"
    new "This man, she thought, seemed to live at the tyrant's every whim. Could he be a good man, even if he worked for the man that enslaved her people?"

    old "They initially joined the line, awaiting their turn, but upon being noticed, Hassar stood up and waived for them to advance ahead of the line."
    new "They initially joined the line, awaiting their turn, but upon being noticed, Hassar stood up and waived for them to advance ahead of the line."

    old "Sarah felt herself dragged forward again. Angry faces, wondering why this slave girl would be allowed to skip the line."
    new "Sarah felt herself dragged forward again. Angry faces, wondering why this slave girl would be allowed to skip the line."

    old "She felt the bindings on her wrists being slipped off."
    new "She felt the bindings on her wrists being slipped off."

    old "A rough push on her lower back caused her to stumble onto the floor. She caught herself only just in time, landing on all fours at the steps of Hassar's throne."
    new "A rough push on her lower back caused her to stumble onto the floor. She caught herself only just in time, landing on all fours at the steps of Hassar's throne."

    old "Her face shot up, full of rage, only to remember her place as her eyes met Hassar's."
    new "Her face shot up, full of rage, only to remember her place as her eyes met Hassar's."

    old "She bowed her head low again."
    new "She bowed her head low again."

    old "The officer made some kind of an announcement. Sarah didn't recognize much of what he said, only her own name. Sarah Rose."
    new "The officer made some kind of an announcement. Sarah didn't recognize much of what he said, only her own name. Sarah Rose."

    old "Hassar rose from his throne."
    new "Hassar rose from his throne."

    old "He descended from the steps and ended up standing over Sarah."
    new "He descended from the steps and ended up standing over Sarah."

    old "Sarah continued to keep her head lowered, staring at the conquerer's feet, hoping that this would somehow spare her."
    new "Sarah continued to keep her head lowered, staring at the conquerer's feet, hoping that this would somehow spare her."

    old "Khan Hassar."
    new "Khan Hassar."

    old "By your orders I have ridden out across the world and carried your word to the kingdom of Rosanna."
    new "By your orders I have ridden out across the world and carried your word to the kingdom of Rosanna."

    old "In their arrogance, they rejected your offer of peace."
    new "In their arrogance, they rejected your offer of peace."

    old "And so, your horde carried out their punishment, and I carried out my vow, bringing you the daughter of their nation."
    new "And so, your horde carried out their punishment, and I carried out my vow, bringing you the daughter of their nation."

    old "Sarah Rose, former princess of Rosanna."
    new "Sarah Rose, former princess of Rosanna."

    old "Thank you Jaeid. Had I but a thousand men like you, this great war of mine would have been won years ago."
    new "Thank you Jaeid. Had I but a thousand men like you, this great war of mine would have been won years ago."

    old "You offer me too great a praise, Khan Hassar."
    new "You offer me too great a praise, Khan Hassar."

    old "Princess Sarah Rose."
    new "Princess Sarah Rose."

    old "Tell me, how long did your family rule Rosanna."
    new "Tell me, how long did your family rule Rosanna."

    old "Sarah gritted her teeth, but refusing to answer this man would only spell disaster."
    new "Sarah gritted her teeth, but refusing to answer this man would only spell disaster."

    old "Centuries. Many centuries."
    new "Centuries. Many centuries."

    old "Hassar threw his head back and let out a loud booming laugh."
    new "Hassar threw his head back and let out a loud booming laugh."

    old "You see, that is the difference between your people and mine."
    new "You see, that is the difference between your people and mine."

    old "You make so much of your titles and traditions. For centuries, the same family, ruling the same spot of dirt. And it actually fills you with pride to say that."
    new "You make so much of your titles and traditions. For centuries, the same family, ruling the same spot of dirt. And it actually fills you with pride to say that."

    old "My clan was nothing before I took the reigns, and should the one after me prove a fool, they will be nothing again."
    new "My clan was nothing before I took the reigns, and should the one after me prove a fool, they will be nothing again."

    old "Here, in the Mayani Desert, one rules by virtue of their skill, not by the luck of their birth."
    new "Here, in the Mayani Desert, one rules by virtue of their skill, not by the luck of their birth."

    old "Slowly, she felt his grip on her collar slip."
    new "Slowly, she felt his grip on her collar slip."

    old "But I did not order my men to bring you to me from across the world for the chance to lecture you."
    new "But I did not order my men to bring you to me from across the world for the chance to lecture you."

    old "I brought you here to ask you a question, and it is a simple one."
    new "I brought you here to ask you a question, and it is a simple one."

    old "Hassar bend down and grabbed Sarah's collar, violently pulling her up to her feet."
    new "Hassar bend down and grabbed Sarah's collar, violently pulling her up to her feet."

    old "The force of his pull on her collar, made her neck snap back. It was now impossible not to make eye contact with Hassar."
    new "The force of his pull on her collar, made her neck snap back. It was now impossible not to make eye contact with Hassar."

    old "Hassar brought up his hand and the ring that was on his finger with it."
    new "Hassar brought up his hand and the ring that was on his finger with it."

    old "The crimson light that shone off the gemstone now swirled inches from Sarah's eyes."
    new "The crimson light that shone off the gemstone now swirled inches from Sarah's eyes."

    old "Tell me, what do you see when you look at the stone on this ring?"
    new "Tell me, what do you see when you look at the stone on this ring?"

    old "Up close, Sarah could feel her eyes drawn into the light of the stone. It's singular crimson colour revealed itself to instead be an endless multitude of ever more nuanced colours of red."
    new "Up close, Sarah could feel her eyes drawn into the light of the stone. It's singular crimson colour revealed itself to instead be an endless multitude of ever more nuanced colours of red."

    old "Every part of her body, if not her soul, reacted to the stone."
    new "Every part of her body, if not her soul, reacted to the stone."

    old "A voice called out from deep within her mind, but it was not her own."
    new "A voice called out from deep within her mind, but it was not her own."

    old "Voice\" \"DECEIVE HIM! OR HE WILL DECEIVE YOU!"
    new "Voice\" \"DECEIVE HIM! OR HE WILL DECEIVE YOU!"

    old "Sarah forced her eyes away from the stone, and faced Hassar."
    new "Sarah forced her eyes away from the stone, and faced Hassar."

    old "Speak honestly, the gemstone shines like bright crimson."
    new "Speak honestly, the gemstone shines like bright crimson."

    old "Staring down Hassar, Sarah made her declaration."
    new "Staring down Hassar, Sarah made her declaration."

    old "It shines like bright crimson."
    new "It shines like bright crimson."

    old "A smile creeped across Hassar's face."
    new "A smile creeped across Hassar's face."

    old "Good. You will learn that I value honesty and loyalty Sarah. Offer me those things, and I will see that your life here need not be so different from the one before."
    new "Good. You will learn that I value honesty and loyalty Sarah. Offer me those things, and I will see that your life here need not be so different from the one before."

    old "Hassar made a subtle motion that Sarah barely noticed."
    new "Hassar made a subtle motion that Sarah barely noticed."

    old "Two guards rushed forward and grabbed Sarah by each arm."
    new "Two guards rushed forward and grabbed Sarah by each arm."

    old "Take her to the sanctum. Any harm that falls to her will fall on you tenfold."
    new "Take her to the sanctum. Any harm that falls to her will fall on you tenfold."

    old "And with that command, Sarah felt herself dragged away from the throne room, whisked away on the warlord's command."
    new "And with that command, Sarah felt herself dragged away from the throne room, whisked away on the warlord's command."

    old "Deceive him. Tell him the stone appears black."
    new "Deceive him. Tell him the stone appears black."

    old "Sarah stared Hassar down."
    new "Sarah stared Hassar down."

    old "She gathered all her skill and managed even now, naked and bound before this monster, to still her heart and calm her emotions."
    new "She gathered all her skill and managed even now, naked and bound before this monster, to still her heart and calm her emotions."

    old "It looks black to me, like obsidian."
    new "It looks black to me, like obsidian."

    old "Hassar inspected her face, his eyes probing for any sign of weakness. But in this moment, Sarah had none."
    new "Hassar inspected her face, his eyes probing for any sign of weakness. But in this moment, Sarah had none."

    old "She was convincing."
    new "She was convincing."

    old "Hassar finally released his grip."
    new "Hassar finally released his grip."

    old "Dissapointing, what a waste."
    new "Dissapointing, what a waste."

    old "Guards, take this useless whore to the auction houses, maybe she'll prove to have some value there."
    new "Guards, take this useless whore to the auction houses, maybe she'll prove to have some value there."

    old "Hassar turned around and walked back up to his throne."
    new "Hassar turned around and walked back up to his throne."

    old "Two guards rushed forward and grabbed both of her arms."
    new "Two guards rushed forward and grabbed both of her arms."

    old "They began to pull her away with such strength that she could not offer any resistance."
    new "They began to pull her away with such strength that she could not offer any resistance."

    old "Please. Sarah thought to herself. Don't let it end like this."
    new "Please. Sarah thought to herself. Don't let it end like this."

    old "But it did."
    new "But it did."

    old "With nobody to protect her, Sarah was dragged off to the auction houses."
    new "With nobody to protect her, Sarah was dragged off to the auction houses."

    old "Suddenly, a voice rang out, causing Hassar to turn around and the guards to cease."
    new "Suddenly, a voice rang out, causing Hassar to turn around and the guards to cease."

    old "Khan Hassar!"
    new "Khan Hassar!"

    old "Jaeid stepped forward."
    new "Jaeid stepped forward."

    old "He motioned a gesture of respect, touching his hands to his shoulders."
    new "He motioned a gesture of respect, touching his hands to his shoulders."

    old "I have served you in this campaign with loyalty, and strived to be an examplar to my fellow soldiers."
    new "I have served you in this campaign with loyalty, and strived to be an examplar to my fellow soldiers."

    old "In all my years, you have known me never to ask anything of you, but I humble myself before you now, and beg you for a reward."
    new "In all my years, you have known me never to ask anything of you, but I humble myself before you now, and beg you for a reward."

    old "Sarah could see Hassar was intrigued."
    new "Sarah could see Hassar was intrigued."

    old "A reward? And here I thought you were above having earthly possessions."
    new "A reward? And here I thought you were above having earthly possessions."

    old "Well, you have been a true servant to me, and you proven yourself in the campaign for Rosanna."
    new "Well, you have been a true servant to me, and you proven yourself in the campaign for Rosanna."

    old "Ask whatever thing you want and you will have it."
    new "Ask whatever thing you want and you will have it."

    old "A pause lingered in the air."
    new "A pause lingered in the air."

    old "Ooh great Khan, I ask you, grant me the slave Sarah Rose."
    new "Ooh great Khan, I ask you, grant me the slave Sarah Rose."

    old "Then that booming laugh of Hassar's rang out through the entire room."
    new "Then that booming laugh of Hassar's rang out through the entire room."

    old "So long and so loud did he laugh, Sarah wondered if the man had lost his mind."
    new "So long and so loud did he laugh, Sarah wondered if the man had lost his mind."

    old "Only when his bout of laughter ended did he finally speak again."
    new "Only when his bout of laughter ended did he finally speak again."

    old "Fine, Jaeid you can have her."
    new "Fine, Jaeid you can have her."

    old "But I'll give you a word of wisdom from an old man, I used to be young like you, dreaming of bedding every princess or queen in the world."
    new "But I'll give you a word of wisdom from an old man, I used to be young like you, dreaming of bedding every princess or queen in the world."

